						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone lying near the village Chāvaḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>16th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This record, in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">16th Century A.D.,</hi> states that the field was the <hi rend="italic">mānya</hi> of Mādapa, son of Gaṁgapa, belonging to Āśvalāyana-sūtra, Atrēya-gōtra and Ṛk-śākhā.</p>						

